summary:
The Security Council:
Reaffirms previous resolutions on East Timor, particularly 1272 (1999) and 1338 (2001);
Commends UNTAET's work and leadership in assisting East Timor's transition to independence;
Recalls the endorsement of the Constituent Assembly's proposal for independence on 20 May 2002;
Welcomes efforts to achieve independence by that date;
Considers the Secretary-General's report of 17 January 2002 and his recommendation to extend UNTAET's mandate;
 Looks forward to proposals for a successor UN mission;
1. Welcomes the Secretary-General's report;
2. Extends UNTAET's mandate until 20 May 2002;
3. Remains seized of the matter.
